</div></div></a><div class="gallery-slide-image-caption"> </div><div class="gallery-slide-number"><span class="gallery-slide-number-current">1</span>/<span class="gallery-slide-number-total">10</span></div><h2 class="gallery-slide-title">Zucchini Gratin</h2><div class="gallery-slide-description"><p>Veggies are always better with a hit of cheese, aren’t they? Thanks to the addition of gruyere and bread crumbs, this dish is guaranteed to make any zucchini naysayer a fan. It’s an easy but impressive dish to serve guests or indulge in alongside barbecued fish or a <a href="https://www.foodnetwork.ca/recipe/air-fryer-roast-chicken/">roasted chicken</a>.</p>
<p>You May Also Like: <a href="https://www.foodnetwork.ca/article/10-trendy-recipes-from-canadas-favourite-cheeses/">10 Trendy Recipes From Canada’s Favourite Cheeses</a></p>


</div><a class="gallery-slide-cta button-primary" target="_blank" href="https://www.foodnetwork.ca/recipe/ina-gartens-zucchini-gratin/">Get the recipe</a></div><div class="gallery-slide"><a class="gallery-slide-image-link" aria-label="Link to Spring Green Spaghetti Carbonara" target="_blank" href="https://www.foodnetwork.ca/recipe/ina-garten-spring-green-spaghetti-carbonara/"><div class="gallery-slide-image"><div class="corus-image-wrapper" style="max-width:1280px;margin:auto"><img alt="a bowl of spaghetti carbonara with green veggies" loading="lazy" width="1280" height="853" decoding="async" data-nimg="1" class="gallery-slide-image-file" style="color:transparent;width:100%;height:auto" sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px" srcSet="https://api.vip.foodnetwork.ca/wp-content/uploads/2022/03/green-spaghetti-feature.jpg?w=640&amp;quality=75 640w, https://api.vip.foodnetwork.ca/wp-content/uploads/2022/03/green-spaghetti-feature.jpg?w=704&amp;quality=75 704w, https://api.vip.foodnetwork.ca/wp-content/uploads/2022/03/green-spaghetti-feature.jpg?w=750&amp;quality=75 750w, https://api.vip.foodnetwork.ca/wp-content/uploads/2022/03/green-spaghetti-feature.jpg?w=828&amp;quality=75 828w, https://api.vip.foodnetwork.ca/wp-content/uploads/2022/03/green-spaghetti-feature.jpg?w=856&amp;quality=75 856w, https://api.vip.foodnetwork.ca/wp-content/uploads/2022/03/green-spaghetti-feature.jpg?w=1080&amp;quality=75 1080w, https://api.vip.foodnetwork.ca/wp-content/uploads/2022/03/green-spaghetti-feature.jpg?w=1200&amp;quality=75 1200w, https://api.vip.foodnetwork.ca/wp-content/uploads/2022/03/green-spaghetti-feature.jpg?w=1920&amp;quality=75 1920w, https://api.vip.foodnetwork.ca/wp-content/uploads/2022/03/green-spaghetti-feature.jpg?w=2048&amp;quality=75 2048w, https://api.vip.foodnetwork.ca/wp-content/uploads/2022/03/green-spaghetti-feature.jpg?w=3840&amp;quality=75 3840w" src="https://api.vip.foodnetwork.ca/wp-content/uploads/2022/03/green-spaghetti-feature.jpg?w=3840&amp;quality=75"/></div></div></a><div class="gallery-slide-image-caption"> </div><div class="gallery-slide-number"><span class="gallery-slide-number-current">2</span>/<span class="gallery-slide-number-total">10</span></div><h2 class="gallery-slide-title">Spring Green Spaghetti Carbonara</h2><div class="gallery-slide-description"><p>Fresh spring veggies like asparagus and peas transform this cold-weather pasta dish into a brighter, warm-weather option. Don’t worry; the pasta still features the egg and pancetta taste you’d expect from traditional <a href="https://www.foodnetwork.ca/recipe/fiery-korean-udon-carbonara/">carbonara</a>, but with an added freshness that eliminates the need for a side salad.</p>


</div><a class="gallery-slide-cta button-primary" target="_blank" href="https://www.foodnetwork.ca/recipe/ina-garten-spring-green-spaghetti-carbonara/">Get the recipe</a></div><div class="gallery-slide"><a class="gallery-slide-image-link" aria-label="Link to Skillet-Roasted Lemon Chicken" target="_blank" href="https://www.foodnetwork.ca/recipe/ina-garten-skillet-roasted-lemon-chicken/"><div class="gallery-slide-image"><div class="corus-image-wrapper" style="max-width:1280px;margin:auto"><img alt="Ina Garten&#x27;s skillet kitchen in a cast iron pan with lemon slices" loading="lazy" width="1280" height="853" decoding="async" data-nimg="1" class="gallery-slide-image-file" style="color:transparent;width:100%;height:auto" sizes="(max-width: 1024px) 100vw, 1024px" srcSet="https://api.vip.foodnetwork.ca/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/ina-skillet-lemon-chicken_1280x853.jpg?w=640&amp;quality=75 640w, https://api.vip.foodnetwork.ca/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/ina-skillet-lemon-chicken_1280x853.jpg?w=704&amp;quality=75 704w, https://api.vip.foodnetwork.ca/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/ina-skillet-lemon-chicken_1280x853.jpg?w=750&amp;quality=75 750w, https://api.vip.foodnetwork.ca/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/ina-skillet-lemon-chicken_1280x853.jpg?w=828&amp;quality=75 828w, https://api.vip.foodnetwork.ca/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/ina-skillet-lemon-chicken_1280x853.jpg?w=856&amp;quality=75 856w, https://api.vip.foodnetwork.ca/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/ina-skillet-lemon-chicken_1280x853.jpg?w=1080&amp;quality=75 1080w, https://api.vip.foodnetwork.ca/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/ina-skillet-lemon-chicken_1280x853.jpg?w=1200&amp;quality=75 1200w, https://api.vip.foodnetwork.ca/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/ina-skillet-lemon-chicken_1280x853.jpg?w=1920&amp;quality=75 1920w, https://api.vip.foodnetwork.ca/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/ina-skillet-lemon-chicken_1280x853.jpg?w=2048&amp;quality=75 2048w, https://api.vip.foodnetwork.ca/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/ina-skillet-lemon-chicken_1280x853.jpg?w=3840&amp;quality=75 3840w" src="https://api.vip.foodnetwork.ca/wp-content/uploads/2021/10/ina-skillet-lemon-chicken_1280x853.jpg?w=3840&amp;quality=75"/></div></div></a><div class="gallery-slide-image-caption"> </div><div class="gallery-slide-number"><span class="gallery-slide-number-current">3</span>/<span class="gallery-slide-number-total">10</span></div><h2 class="gallery-slide-title">Skillet-Roasted Lemon Chicken</h2><div class="gallery-slide-description"><p><a href="https://www.foodnetwork.ca/tag/chicken/">Chicken</a> is delicious any time of year, but Ina Garten’s roast chicken with lemon has a definite spring vibe. With a <a href="https://www.foodnetwork.ca/article/michael-symon-how-to-clean-cast-iron-pans/">cast iron pan</a> and a few fresh herbs, you can roast chicken any day of the week with this recipe. Of course, we think it’s still an impressive dish to serve to guests, especially when you pair it with a fresh salad and a bottle of white.</p>
<p>You May Also Like: <a href="https://www.foodnetwork.ca/article/ways-to-use-leftover-rotisserie-chicken/">10 Ways to Use a Leftover Rotisserie Chicken</a></p>


