aeli-Vegetable-Salad-Featured.jpg?w=3840&amp;quality=75"/></div></div></a><div class="gallery-slide-image-caption"> </div><div class="gallery-slide-number"><span class="gallery-slide-number-current">5</span>/<span class="gallery-slide-number-total">10</span></div><h2 class="gallery-slide-title">Israeli Vegetable Salad</h2><div class="gallery-slide-description"><p><a href="https://www.foodnetwork.ca/recipe/hummus-with-spiced-ground-beef/">Hummus</a> is more than a dip: when you combine it with fresh veggies and herbs, it can serve as a dressing for an incredible salad. That’s what Ina does in this lemony dish, which includes bell peppers, cucumbers, cherry tomatoes and a little Sriracha for kick.</p>
